name: Wasteland Fork of Warlock Canyon
description:
Introduction

went back to complete another fork of Warlock Canyon, done in 2012. This time we also did a new ascent adjacent to the canyon from the south side. The new fork had eight new rappels to build anchors for, up to 140' high before it joined up with the known canyon (Warlock Canyon)

Background

12-20-14 - New fork of Warlock Canyon completed as a First Descent Exploration by Scott Swaney and team - see trip report above for details. Also ascended up a new route up the West ridge to see how it compares with the original way up.
